Description:
Contemporary class, lifestyle ease
Clean lines and quality appointments make this near-new three bedroom two bathroom residence a standout for astute buyers keen on low maintenance living. Big on space, open plan living featuring solid hardwood floors and a designer two-tone CaesarStone island kitchen complete with full suite of stainless steel appliances opens to manicured low maintenance gardens showcasing built-in seating, quaint vertical garden and alfresco area for your entertaining pleasure. Excellence continues through carpeted bedrooms, designer bathrooms with oversized showers and stone topped vanities, master with ensuite and WIR, spacious laundry, powder room, plantation shutters, heating/cooling and garage with remote plus OSP. Enviably positioned a short walk to Centreway shops, cafes and Milleara Road buses, with easy access to the Calder and associated freeways and range of schools including Penleigh & Essendon Grammar, Keilor Heights Primary and Essendon Keilor College, inspection will impress.

Description:
Fully-Optioned Low-Maintenance Luxury Living!
With its free-flowing design, premium inclusions and immaculate gardens all-round, this brand-new single-level sensation delivers a lifestyle of easy-living excellence along with immediate access to the best of Keilor Park. Meticulous attention to detail, the home's quality interior showcases three bedrooms (large master) all with fitted full-width robes, deluxe ensuite and equally-stylish central bathroom - both with stone-top vanities and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a dedicated study area and spacious open-plan living/dining accompanied by European equipped kitchen complete with stone benchtops and walk-in butler's pantry. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, square-set ceilings with LED lighting, secured alarm system, video-com, solid hardwood floors, large windows and soft-close cabinetry throughout, plus an impressive decked alfresco back garden, internally-accessed garage (r/c) and additional driveway parking. A short stroll to shops, cafes, buses, Steele Creek trails and parkland as well as easy access to the Calder Freeway.

Description:
Hidden Haven
Nestled in a boutique development with well kept grounds, this two bedroom villa unit is tucked back from the street, cleverly designed and graced with a peaceful garden haven. Immediately upon opening the door you'll be met with a relaxing ambience and generous design. Seamlessly transitioning from living to dining zones, leisure spaces are linked to the kitchen by a breakfast bar and to the tranquil and colourful rear garden by sliding glass door. Fully equipped, the kitchen flaunts excellent counter space and a pantry plus appliances ranging from a gas cooktop to a fan forced oven and dishwasher. Bedrooms each offer a large BIR or WIR, and the dual entry bathroom has a bath and separate shower plus direct access to the main bedroom. Ducted heating and reverse cycle air conditioning enhance comfort, and parking is provided in a garage with interior access. Stroll to transport, schools, Rose Creek Reserve, local shops and lively Keilor Road from the highly desirable position.

Description:
Ultra-Connected & Low Maintenance Modern Unit!
Enjoy low-maintenance living surrounded by local amenities in this modern 3-bedroom unit with stylish and comfortable features throughout!
Privately positioned at the rear of the block, theres 185m2 of living space perfectly suited to downsizers and young families.
High ceilings and stunning white tiles set a modern tone in the light-filled open plan living and dining area, which also includes LED downlights and air conditioning throughout. The sleek kitchen features a dishwasher, stainless steel appliances and plenty of storage space in the striking dark cabinetry.
High-quality stone benchtops can be found in the kitchen and full central bathroom, which services the 3 good-sized bedrooms with floorboards and built-in wardrobes. A space-saving internal laundry sits adjacent to the kitchen.
Step outside to find a spacious low maintenance backyard and pergola area offering plenty of room for outdoor entertaining. A lock-up carport provides secure parking for 1 car, with extra driveway parking available for guests.
This ultra-convenient central location is just a short walk from Keilor Central Shopping Centre, St Albans Leisure Centre and Keilor Plains train station, with easy access to local schools, bus stops and other amenities for easy family living.
Take advantage of this fantastic opportunity for stylish low-maintenance living with unbeatable connections. Call Nathan Chu on 0490 049 645 to arrange your inspection today!

Address: Lot 319 (Taylors Qua Lipizzan Crescent Taylors Lakes VIC 3038
Description:
Lot 319 - Lipizzan Crescent (Taylors Quarter)
Taylors Quarter is the last major land release in the heart of Taylors Lakes. Live walking distance to schools, parks, Watergardens Shopping Centre and the Watergardens Train Station.
This is a rare opportunity to secure land to build your ideal home. Create a garden oasis perfect for alfresco dining to entertain family and friends, or lounge by the pool in deck chairs with a cool drink.
At Taylors Quarter your options are endless.
Due to the success of previously balloted stages the same ballot sales process will be in place for Stage 10 & 11.
Please read this process entirely and be sure to contact our sales team should you have any questions.
If you have already registered you will automatically be entered the Stage 10 & 11 ballot, unless you specifically request otherwise.
STAGE 10 & 11 SALES PROCESS
1) Stage 10 & 11 (15 lots) will be released via ballot at 9am, Saturday February 8 at the Taylors Quarter Sales Office, McCubbin Drive, Taylors Lakes.
2) To participate in the ballot, you must first register by paying a $5,000 registration fee in person at the Taylors Quarter Sales Office. The registration payment can be used towards the deposit. Registrations will open at 11am Friday January 31 and close at 4pm Friday February 7. No ballot registrations will be accepted prior to this date or on the day of the ballot.
3) Registered parties are to arrive at the Taylors Quarter Sales Office by 8:30am on Saturday February 8. The ballot will be drawn from 9am, names will be called, and you will have the opportunity to select your preferred lot. Due to strong demand, we advise that you should have an alternative should your desired lot not be available. Only one lot can be purchased per registration and the name drawn on the ballot must be the same name that appears on the contract. If the person signing the contract doesn't have the same name as the one drawn in the ballot, the Sales Consultant will have the right to cancel the hold and reallocate the lot to the next eligible person, unless otherwise approved. Transferring your right to choose a lot is not permitted. Multiple registrations are not permitted.
4) Successful parties will need to pay the balance of the10% deposit required to purchase the lot and sign an unconditional contract of sale by 4pm on Sunday February 9 (or as per terms agreed to by the sales agent on the day). Successful persons are entitled to purchase one lot only. Only one lot per household may be purchased on the day, unless lots remain unsold after the ballot process.
5) All payments can be made payable to Core Projects (VIC) Pty Ltd (Development Victorias appointed Sales Agent) - or via bank transfer (EFT). Registration deposits can be made with a Visa or Mastercard. Cash will not be accepted, and valid photo identification will be requested upon signing and receipts will be issued. Importantly, payment must be made from within the Sales Office on McCubbin Drive from an account under the same name as the signatory of the contract.
EFT payment details can be found at taylorsquarter.com.au/news
6) Parties who are unsuccessful in the ballot have the option of a full refund of their $5,000 ballot registration fee within 5 business days, or to remain registered in the ballot process for future stage releases.
